China Stocks Valuations May Get Boost if CPI Below 4%

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-22T04:30:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/china-stocks-valuations-may-get-boost-if-cpi-below-4-correct-.html
(Corrects Ling’s title in first paragraph.)  Chinese stocks’ valuations may get a
boost if the inflation rate drops below 4 percent this year on
expectations monetary policies may ease, Ling Peng, chief
strategist of Shenyin and Wanguo Securities Co., said today at
an investment conference in Guiyang, southwestern  China .  Ling favors property stocks because of increasing sales. He
also likes coal and cement stocks because supply shortages will
boost prices, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
